  <description>
    A simple implementation of JNDI. It is entirely library based, so no server instances are started, and it sits upon Java .properties files, XML files or .ini files, so it is easy to use and simple to understand. The .properties/.xml/.ini files may be either on the file system or in the classpath.
  </description>
